CCDD

Class CcddClassesDataTable.TableInformation

  • java.lang.Object
    • CCDD.CcddClassesDataTable.TableInformation
  • Enclosing class:
    CcddClassesDataTable

    protected static class CcddClassesDataTable.TableInformation
extends java.lang.Object
    Table information class A table can be one (or possibly more) of the following: prototype, root, parent, and child. A prototype table is produced whenever the Data | New table(s) menu command is used to create a table. The prototype becomes a 'rubber stamp' for creating other table instances that initially contain the same information as the prototype. A root table is a prototype that is not referenced from within another table (making it a top level table). Therefore a root table is always a prototype table, but the reverse isn't necessarily true. Other tables may be referenced within the root table - these referenced tables are known as child tables. A table's parent table is the table in which the child table is directly referenced. The parent table can itself be a child table, or the parent and root tables are the same in the case where the child is referenced directly in the root table

      • TableInformation

        TableInformation(java.lang.String tableType,
                 java.lang.String tablePath,
                 java.lang.Object[][] tableData,
                 java.lang.String columnOrder,
                 java.lang.String description)
        Table information class constructor
        Parameters:
        tableType - table type
        tablePath - table path in the format rootTable[,dataType1.variable1[,dataType2 .variable2[,...]]]. The table path for a non-structure table is simply the root table name. For a structure table the root table is the top level structure table from which this table descends. The first data type/variable name pair is from the root table, with each succeeding pair coming from the next level down in the structure's hierarchy
        tableData - two-dimensional table data array (rows x columns)
        columnOrder - table column display order in the format column#0[:column#1[:...[:column#N]]]. The column numbers are based on the position of the column's definition in the table's type definition
        description - table description
